   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "Pointing two peers at each other via the \"addnode\" / \"connect\" args in bitcoin.conf on init results in multiple (3 as observed in getpeerinfo on regtest) connections (on different ports) and, hence, chatty traffic (say inventory exchange) when running off of the current master. Connecting via the \"addnode\" RPC call after a successful initialization of both peers corrects this.\n",
